main event: Unidentified lights were observed in the sky over Kingfisher, Oklahoma on September 24, 1954.
interesting points: The objects were observed on several occasions, flying in a 'VV' formation.
The objects were larger than jet aircraft and appeared to be solid, with their undersides illuminated.
The objects were faster than jet aircraft.
The length of the observation and the exact number of objects were unknown.
No photographs were taken of the incident.
